{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ec3354c9-bbcd-4632-b570-4cdf76f2f20e","content":"The issue is classic F#: **file compilation order matters**. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` in the `.fsproj`, but it depends on types defined in `Domain.fs`. F# requires dependencies to appear earlier in the file list.\n\nFixing by reordering `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_CJSwfO7Lcb5xPxcQCHdkOb","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2863ac030d6146baa74373baab066ac9/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-2863ac030d6146baa74373baab066ac9/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"cf0ee459-987f-4c08-8ff0-c2127338942f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — depends on `Domain.fs` (uses `Order`, `OrderId` types)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — depends on both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. So `Domain.fs` must come first.\n\n\nI need to reorder the files so that `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, and finally `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":434,"requestId":"5C37:11463F:605437B:691C636:69F15607"},"id":"8dce2f88-47ae-408c-a3f2-e217d86899e4","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:28.627Z","parentId":"55cbcaa4-6859-42d2-abaa-bf10d9568264"}
